# Bosowa Agent (Python)

- **Process lifecycle**: `force_lock` and similar paths must ensure the agent comes back after exit — use detached `relaunch_agent_process()` (see `agent/utils/relaunch.py`) instead of relying only on Task Scheduler logon triggers.
- **Lock message**: Persist reason with flush/fsync (`store_lock_message`) before exit so the new process can read it for the overlay.
- **Socket**: Join rooms with MAC format consistent with portal normalization; avoid duplicate connections leaking heartbeats.
- **Audit**: Batch LINK/APP (and related) events through the audit client; respect flush intervals and pruning expectations aligned with portal ingest.
- **Overlay**: Opening the portal/login from lockscreen should emit LINK audit events when applicable.
